TWO football thugs were given one year football banning orders yesterday after violence flared at a Queen of the South v Rangers match.
James Meehan and Robert Patterson were slapped with the orders after the trouble at the game on Saturday.
At Dumfries and Galloway Sheriff Court, Meehan, 23, from Glasgow, pled guilty to assault and was also hit with a &pound;300 fine.
Patterson, 25, from Dumfries, pled guilty to a breach of the peace and also received a community payback order.
